mcqs.question:
What is the output of the following recursive function for n=5?

int fun(int n) {
    if (n == 0) return 1;
    return n * fun(n - 1);
}

What is missing in the following recursive function to prevent infinite recursion?

void countDown(int n) {
    printf("%d ", n);
    countDown(n - 1);
}

What type of recursion is shown below?

int fun(int n) {
    if (n == 0) return 0;
    return fun(n - 1) + n;
}

What is the output of this code?

int fun(int n) {
    if (n > 0) {
        printf("%d ", n);
        fun(n - 1);
    }
}

int main() {
    fun(3);
    return 0;
}

What is the return value of fun(3)?

int fun(int n) {
    if (n == 0 || n == 1) return n;
    return fun(n-1) + fun(n-2);
}
